### How to use

## Create a `.vimrc` file in your home folder and add this content.

```
source $HOME/.vim/vim-plug/plugins.vim

source $HOME/.vim/general/settings.vim

source $HOME/.vim/keys/mappings.vim

source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/coc.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/fugitive.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/fzf.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/gv.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/nerdtree.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/rhubarb.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/rnvimr.vim
source $HOME/.vim/plug-config/signify.vim

source $HOME/.vim/themes/airline.vim
source $HOME/.vim/themes/onedark.vim
```